HEADWORD: Pantechnicon
<hw>Pan*tech"ni*con</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Pan-</er>, and <er>Technic</er>.]</ety> <def>A depository or place
where all sorts of manufactured articles are collected for
sale.</def>⟦br⟧
